&lt;h3 id=&quot;i-would-like-to-thank-these-post-authors-for-writing-these-resources-they-helped-me-a-lot&quot;&gt;I would like to thank these post authors for writing these resources, they helped me a lot:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://24ways.org/2013/get-started-with-github-pages/&quot;&gt;Get Started With GitHub Pages (Plus Bonus Jekyll)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://andytaylor.me/2012/11/03/installing-ruby-and-jekyll/&quot;&gt;Installing Ruby &amp;amp; Jekyll on Mac OS X&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Though I would like to point out some errors on Andy Taylor’s blog post, they were probably outdated:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct command for installing Homebrew:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;ruby -e &quot;$(curl -fsSL https://raw.github.com/Homebrew/homebrew/go/install)&quot;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
If this is not working you can always refer to the updated command on &lt;a href=&quot;http://brew.sh/&quot;&gt;Homebrew’s page&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct command for starting Jekyll server:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;jekyll serve&lt;/code&gt; not &lt;code&gt;jekyll --server&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also came across &lt;a href=&quot;http://prose.io&quot;&gt;Prose.io&lt;/a&gt;, a content Editor for Github which allows users to preview the changes directly on Markdown, and it could function similar to Wordpress editor, which I am used to for writing blog posts. You can read more about Prose.io &lt;a href=&quot;developmentseed.org/blog/2012/june/25/prose-a-content-editor-for-github/&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

